Production of the comedy The Taming of the Shrew will take place at the Artscape Theatre and various schools. The youngsters were given an opportunity to learn from a professional cast who will also be starring in the production, which starts today, 7 February 2018, at Maynardville Open Air Theatre. The pupils will get a chance to chat to the cast and creative team of The Taming of the Shrew. It’s the first all-female production to take place at Maynardville in its 62-year history. The students will also discuss the process and different aspects of staging a production, to help with their own presentation, which is also The Taming of the Shrew.    The professional production is directed by Tara Notcutt. It forms part of the inaugural Maynardville Open-Air Festival and features an exciting programme of music, dance, comedy and more under the stars at Maynardville. Notcutt leads some of South Africa’s most celebrated actresses in this play.  argusnews@inl.co.za  Cape Argus